<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25679</anchor> <rss>anon.175.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.175</addr>  <route>anon.175.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We first prove the lemma for <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> functions, so that both the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> are tracked by <tex>g</tex>. In this case, we may use <link href="erct-0016.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0016" title="Singleton induction">singleton induction</link> via the <link href="erct-001D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001D" title="The univalence principle for types">univalence principle for types</link> to restrict attention to the case that <tex>f</tex> is the identity map, and the result is immediate.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25680</anchor> <rss>erct-001S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001S</addr>  <route>erct-001S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Pushforward of <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path objects</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001S.agda" type="external">erct-001S.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> has a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <tex>g \colon  B  \to  A</tex>, then a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> structure on <tex>A</tex> induces a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> structure on <tex>B</tex>, setting <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( x  \cong _B y \right ) \mathclose {}  : \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( gx \cong _A gy \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25681</anchor> <rss>erct-001D.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-001D</addr>  <route>erct-001D.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for types</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001D.agda" type="external">erct-001D.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The reflexive graph structure on types given by <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalences</link> is <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">univalent</link>. We shall write <tex>\mathsf {Type}</tex> to indicate the resulting (large) path object of types and <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalences</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25682</anchor> <rss>erct-000U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr>  <route>erct-000U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25683</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr>  <route>erct-000Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sections and retractions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25684</anchor> <rss>erct-0016.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Theorem</taxon> <addr>erct-0016</addr>  <route>erct-0016.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Singleton induction</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0016.agda" type="external">erct-0016.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> type with centre <tex>a</tex>. For any family of types <tex>B \colon  A  \to   \mathsf {Type}</tex>, we may define a function <tex>\mathsf {ind}_{ A,a } \colon  B a  \to   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x : A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x : A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x : A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x : A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> satisfying <tex>\mathsf {ind}_{ A,a } \, b \, a = b</tex>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25685</anchor> <rss>anon.184.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.184</addr>  <route>anon.184.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Let <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> be the witness of contraction for any <tex>x:A</tex>. Given <tex>b : Ba</tex> and <tex>x:A</tex>, we define <tex>\mathsf {ind}_{ A,a } \, b \, x : Bx</tex> by transporting <tex>b</tex> along the identification <tex>\chi _a ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex>:</p>

  <tex display="block">
     \mathsf {ind}_{ A,a } \, b \, x : \equiv 
     \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _a ^{-1} \cdot \chi _x \right ) \mathclose {} _* b
  </tex>

  <p>Then we compute <tex>\mathsf {ind}_{ A,a } \, b \, x  \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _a ^{-1} \cdot \chi _a \right ) \mathclose {} _* b  =  \mathsf {refl} _*b = b</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
